  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Dear Sir, I received your letter of —— acknowledging the receipt of my work on the mysteries including Freemasonry — stating that you had not fully perused it and therefore had not made up your option in regard to the probability of the sale of a republication of it in England.</p>
         <p>The bearer of this resides in this city, and will soon return. I should like to hear farther from you on the subject by him.</p>
         <p>We understand that you are lecturing on the holy scriptures, showing them to be mainly allegorical— I have <persName>Sir William Drummond's</persName> work on the subjects; and find it very plaussible [sic] in respect to many parts of this holy book. This fact being proved renders the bible null and void as to its inspiration.</p>
         <p>I am now concerned in the editing of a liberal work, entitled the Beacon – of which I send you the numbers as far printed.—</p>
            <p>The bearer is waiting —</p>
            <p>yours sincerely</p>
            <p>John Fellows</p>
